article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 76, Tennessee St. 74
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Reserve Gerald Robinson scored 32 points and Tennessee-Martin held off Tennessee State for a 76-74 win Tuesday night. Tennessee-Martin (7-20, 5-12 Ohio Valley Conference) led the last 1:08 after Cleve Woodfork made a jumper to go ahead 69-67. He hit two free throws with 15 seconds left to put the Skyhawks up 73-68. Robinson was 11-of-21 from the floor, including 7-of-11 3-pointers, in 31 minutes of play. Tennessee State (10-15, 6-9 OVC) was led by reserve Ladarious Weaver with 26 points, Clarence Matthews with 16 points and a team-high eight rebounds and Andrae Belton with 12 points. For the Skyhawks, McClenon Tolliver had 16 points including three free throws in the last seven seconds that kept the visitors ahead. Woodfork finished with 13 points and was 5-of-5 from the floor. Tennessee-Martin made 17-of-29 free throws to 7-of-11 for the Tigers. The Skyhawks shot 58.1 percent including 63.6 percent in the second half. Tennessee State shot 46.6 percent.
